%section.tbs-section
  %h1.page-header#fa Icons (Font Awesome)
  %p.lead
    TED Bootstrap includes Font Awesome
    = succeed ',' do
      %a{href: 'http://fortawesome.github.io/Font-Awesome/'}<
        Font Awesome
    which provides a huge library of versatile icons.

  %h2#glyphicons-list Icon list
  %p
    A complete list of icons provided by Font Awesome
    = succeed '.' do
      %a{href: 'http://fortawesome.github.io/Font-Awesome/icons/'}<
        is maintained here
    All of these icons are available in TED Bootstrap,
    and a Rails Helper is also provided.

  %h2#glyphicons-example How to use

  %h3#glyphicons-example-helper Rails helper
  %p
    The Rails helper
    %code icon
    allows you to drop icons just about anywhere.
    It takes three parameters

  %ol
    %li
      The name of the icon
      %em without
      the
      %code fa-
      prefix.
    %li
      A label, or nil or an empty string if no label is needed
    %li
      A hash of other attributes to apply to the tag.

  %p Examples:

  :markdown
          = icon 'flag'
          # => <i class="fa fa-flag"></i>

  :markdown
          = icon 'flag', '', class: 'strong'
          # => <i class="fa fa-flag strong"></i>

  :markdown
          = icon 'flag', 'Font Awesome', id: 'my-icon', class: 'strong'
          # => <i id="my-icon" class="fa fa-flag strong"></i> Font Awesome

  %p Examples within Bootstrap elements:

  .tbs-example
    %button.btn.btn-danger
      = icon 'trash-o', 'Delete', class: 'fa-lg'

    .btn-group
      %a.btn.btn-default{href: '#'}
        = icon 'user', 'User', class: 'fa-fw'
      %a.btn.btn-default.dropdown-toggle{data: {toggle: 'dropdown'}, href: '#'}
        = icon 'caret-down'
      %ul.dropdown-menu
        %li
          %a{href: '#'}
            = icon 'pencil', 'Edit', class: 'fa-fw'
        %li
          %a{href: '#'}
            = icon 'trash-o', 'Delete', class: 'fa-fw'
        %li
          %a{href: '#'}
            = icon 'ban', 'Ban', class: 'fa-fw'
        %li.divider
        %li
          %a{href: '#'}
            Make admin
  .highlight
