              %li.divider
              %li
                %a{href: '#'}
                  Make admin

  %h2#glyphicons-example-variations Icon variations
  %p
    Font Awesome includes additional CSS classes to control
    icon size and provide stacking, spinning, and other
    icon features.

  %h3#glyphicons-example-variations-sizing Sizing icons
  .row
    .col-sm-4
      %p
        = icon 'camera-retro', '@ lg', class: 'fa-lg'
      %p
        = icon 'camera-retro', '@ 2x', class: 'fa-2x'
      %p
        = icon 'camera-retro', '@ 3x', class: 'fa-3x'
      %p
        = icon 'camera-retro', '@ 4x', class: 'fa-4x'
      %p
        = icon 'camera-retro', '@ 5x', class: 'fa-5x'
    .col-sm-8
      :markdown
        To increase icon sizes relative to their container,
        use the `fa-lg` (33% increase),
        `fa-2x`, `fa-3x`, `fa-4x`, or `fa-5x` classes.

            = icon 'camera-retro', '', class: 'fa-lg'
            = icon 'camera-retro', '', class: 'fa-2x'
            = icon 'camera-retro', '', class: 'fa-3x'
            = icon 'camera-retro', '', class: 'fa-4x'
            = icon 'camera-retro', '', class: 'fa-5x'

  %h3#glyphicons-example-variations-fw Fixed width icons
  .row
    .col-sm-4
      %ul.nav.nav-pills.nav-stacked
        %li.active
          %a{href: '#'}
            = icon 'home', 'Home', class: 'fa-fw'
        %li
          %a{href: '#'}
            = icon 'book', 'Library', class: 'fa-fw'
        %li
          %a{href: '#'}
            = icon 'pencil', 'Applications', class: 'fa-fw'
        %li
          %a{href: '#'}
            = icon 'cogs', 'Settings', class: 'fa-fw'
    .col-sm-8
      :markdown
        Use `fa-fw` to set icons at a fixed width.
        Great to use when variable icon widths throw off alignment.
        Especially useful in things like nav lists.

            %ul.nav.nav-pills.nav-stacked
              %li.active
                %a{href: '#'}
                  = icon 'home', 'Home', class: 'fa-fw'
              %li
                %a{href: '#'}
                  = icon 'book', 'Library', class: 'fa-fw'
              %li
                %a{href: '#'}
                  = icon 'pencil', 'Applications', class: 'fa-fw'
              %li
                %a{href: '#'}
                  = icon 'cogs', 'Settings', class: 'fa-fw'

  %h3#glyphicons-example-variations-lists List icons
  .row
    .col-sm-4
      %ul.fa-ul
        %li= icon 'check-square', 'List icons (like these)', class: 'fa-li'
        %li= icon 'check-square', 'can be used', class: 'fa-li'
        %li= icon 'spinner', 'to replace', class: 'fa-li fa-spin'
        %li= icon 'square', 'default bullets in lists', class: 'fa-li'
    .col-sm-8
      :markdown
        Use `fa-ul` and `fa-li`
        to easily replace default bullets in unordered lists.

            %ul.fa-ul
              %li= icon 'check-square', 'List icons (like these)', class: 'fa-li'
              %li= icon 'check-square', 'can be used', class: 'fa-li'
              %li= icon 'spinner', 'to replace', class: 'fa-li fa-spin'
              %li= icon 'square', 'default bullets in lists', class: 'fa-li'

  %h3#glyphicons-example-variations-spinning Spinning icons
  .row
    .col-sm-4
      %button.btn.btn-default.btn-lg
        = icon 'spinner', nil, class: 'fa-spin'
      %button.btn.btn-default.btn-lg
        = icon 'refresh', nil, class: 'fa-spin'
      %button.btn.btn-default.btn-lg
        = icon 'cog', nil, class: 'fa-spin'
    .col-sm-8
      :markdown
        Add the `fa-spin` class to get any icon to rotate.
        Works well with `spinner`, `refresh`, and `cog` icons.

            = icon 'spinner', nil, class: 'fa-spin'
            = icon 'refresh', nil, class: 'fa-spin'
            = icon 'cog', nil, class: 'fa-spin'

  %h3#glyphicons-example-variations-flipping Rotating &amp; flipping icons
  .row
    .col-sm-4
      %ul.fa-ul
        %li= icon 'shield', 'normal', class: 'fa-li'
        %li= icon 'shield', 'fa-rotate-90', class: 'fa-rotate-90 fa-li'
        %li= icon 'shield', 'fa-rotate-180', class: 'fa-rotate-180 fa-li'
        %li= icon 'shield', 'fa-rotate-270', class: 'fa-rotate-270 fa-li'
        %li= icon 'shield', 'fa-flip-horizontal', class: 'fa-flip-horizontal fa-li'
        %li= icon 'shield', 'fa-flip-vertical', class: 'fa-flip-vertical fa-li'
    .col-sm-8
      :markdown
        To arbitrarily rotate and flip icons, use the
        `fa-rotate-*` and `fa-flip-*` classes.

            = icon 'shield', '', class: 'fa-rotate-90'
            = icon 'shield', '', class: 'fa-rotate-180'
            = icon 'shield', '', class: 'fa-rotate-270'
            = icon 'shield', '', class: 'fa-flip-horizontal'
            = icon 'shield', '', class: 'fa-flip-vertical'

  %h3#glyphicons-example-variations-stacking Stacking icons
  .row
    .col-sm-4
      %span.fa-stack.fa-lg
        = icon 'square-o', '', class: 'fa-stack-2x'
        = icon 'twitter', '', class: 'fa-stack-1x'
      twitter on square-o
      %br
      %span.fa-stack.fa-lg
        = icon 'circle', '', class: 'fa-stack-2x'
        = icon 'flag', '', class: 'fa-stack-1x fa-inverse'
      flag on circle inverse
      %br
      %span.fa-stack.fa-lg
        = icon 'square', '', class: 'fa-stack-2x'
        = icon 'terminal', '', class: 'fa-stack-1x fa-inverse'
      square on terminal inverse
      %br
      %span.fa-stack.fa-lg
        = icon 'camera', '', class: 'fa-stack-1x'
        = icon 'ban', '', class: 'fa-stack-2x text-danger'
      ban on camera
    .col-sm-8
      :markdown
        To stack multiple icons, use the `fa-stack` class
        on the parent,
        the `fa-stack-1x` for the regularly sized icon,
        and `fa-stack-2x` for the larger icon.

            %span.fa-stack.fa-lg
              = icon 'square-o', '', class: 'fa-stack-2x'
              = icon 'twitter', '', class: 'fa-stack-1x'

      :markdown
            %span.fa-stack.fa-lg
              = icon 'circle', '', class: 'fa-stack-2x'
              = icon 'flag', '', class: 'fa-stack-1x fa-inverse'

      :markdown
            %span.fa-stack.fa-lg
              = icon 'square', '', class: 'fa-stack-2x'
              = icon 'terminal', '', class: 'fa-stack-1x fa-inverse'

      :markdown
            %span.fa-stack.fa-lg
              = icon 'camera', '', class: 'fa-stack-1x'
              = icon 'ban', '', class: 'fa-stack-2x text-danger'
